1. `src/db/database.server.ts` - server-only module that:
   - Opens/creates the SQLite database file in the project
   - Seeds it with 47 posts
   - Exports functions to query posts

2. `src/routes/index.tsx` - the home route:
   - `routeLoader$` to get the first page (10 posts) on the server
   - `server$()` function `loadMore` that accepts a cursor and returns next page + hasMore
   - Component with `useStore` to accumulate posts
   - `useVisibleTask$` with IntersectionObserver watching the sentinel
   - Loading indicator, end-of-feed indicator, sentinel element with data-testid attributes

Let me think about the database file location. The vite config comment suggests better-sqlite3 should be in optimizeDeps.exclude. Let me add that too.

Let me think about the server-only module. In Qwik, files named `*.server.ts` are automatically excluded from the client bundle. So I'll create `src/db/database.server.ts`.

Let me design the database module:

```ts
import Database from "better-sqlite3";
import { resolve } from "node:path";

const DB_PATH = resolve(process.cwd(), "feed.db");

let dbInstance: Database.Database | null = null;

function getDb() {
  if (dbInstance) return dbInstance;
  const db = new Database(DB_PATH);
  db.exec(`
    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS posts (
      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
      title TEXT NOT NULL,
      body TEXT NOT NULL
    )
  `);
  // Seed
  const count = db.prepare("SELECT COUNT(*) as c FROM posts").get() as any;
  if (count.c === 0) {
    const insert = db.prepare("INSERT INTO posts (title, body) VALUES (?, ?)");
    const tx = db.transaction(() => {
      for (let n = 1; n <= 47; n++) {
        insert.run(`Post #${n}`, `This is the body text for post number ${n}. ...`);
      }
    });
    tx();
  }
  dbInstance = db;
  return db;
}

export interface Post {
  id: number;
  title: string;
  body: string;
}

export interface PageResult {
  posts: Post[];
  hasMore: boolean;
}

const PAGE_SIZE = 10;

export function getFirstPage(): PageResult {
  const db = getDb();
  const posts = db.prepare("SELECT * FROM posts ORDER BY id ASC LIMIT ?").all(PAGE_SIZE) as Post[];
  const hasMore = (db.prepare("SELECT COUNT(*) as c FROM posts").get() as any).c > posts.length;
  return { posts, hasMore };
}

export function getNextPage(cursor: number): PageResult {
  const db = getDb();
  const posts = db.prepare("SELECT * FROM posts WHERE id > ? ORDER BY id ASC LIMIT ?").all(cursor, PAGE_SIZE) as Post[];
  const lastId = posts.length ? posts[posts.length - 1].id : cursor;
  const hasMore = (db.prepare("SELECT COUNT(*) as c FROM posts WHERE id > ?").get(lastId) as any).c > 0;
  return { posts, hasMore };
}
```

Wait, the seeding: "for every integer N from 1 to 47 there must be a post whose title is exactly Post #N". Using AUTOINCREMENT, the ids will be 1..47, which matches "ordered by ascending post id". Good. But to be safe, I'll insert with explicit id to guarantee ids 1..47.

Actually let me insert with explicit ids to be safe.

Now the route. Let me think about how routeLoader$ and server$ work together.

The routeLoader$ runs on the server during SSR and provides initial data. The server$ function is an RPC callable from the client.

In Qwik City, `routeLoader$` provides data via a signal. The server$ function can be defined in the same file or a server module.

